the horses of SS officers. In Auschwitz he learned and used survival skills that he later applied in the commercial realm. George settled in Montreal and became a world-class wrestler, competing internationally and carrying the flag for the Canadian team at the 1957 Maccabiah Games in Israel. After working in a number of jobs he found his calling in the furniture business, eventually founding Jaymar Furniture, a leading manufacturer and a company that still operates successfully in Quebec. Wrestling with Life is a moving account of a child’s survival under the most difficult of circumstances. It tells the story of one man’s hard-won success as a businessman and athlete.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aBusinesspeoplezQuébec (Province)zMontréalvBiography. 0aHolocaust survivorszQuébec (Province)vBiography. 0aHolocaust survivorszQuébec (Province)zMontréalvBiography. 0aHolocaust, Jewish (1939-1945)zHungaryvPersonal narratives. 0aJewszHungaryvBiography. 0aPhilanthropistszQuébec (Province)vBiography. 0aPhilanthropistszQuébec (Province)zMontréalvBiography. 0aWrestlerszQuébec (Province)zMontréalvBiography. 0vBiography.aJewszHungary. 0vBiography.zQuébec (Province)aBusinesspeople. 0zHungaryvPersonal narratives.aHolocaust, Jewish (1939-1945). 0zQuébec (Province)aWrestlersvBiography. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Business.2bisacsh1 aKing, Richard, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311127365508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2017z978311127619940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978077355183140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780773551831423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780773551831/original  a978-3-11-